|---|---|
| Action type | Composite |
| Logic language | Go (stdlib only) |
| Version source of truth | `version` file |
| Initial version | `0.0.1` |
| Bump strategy | Patch only |
| Version format | `1.2.3` (no `v` prefix) |
| Git tag format | `1.2.3` (no `v` prefix) |
| Docker image name | Derived from repo name |
| Git identity | `github-actions[bot]` |
| Action outputs | `new_version`, `image_name` |
| Allowed dependencies | GitHub official actions, Docker org actions |
| Example workflow | Yes, in `examples/workflow.yml` |
| Permissions | Documented, `contents: write` required |

QUESTION: Does this checklist look correct? If so, I'm ready to write the implementation plan and start coding.
ANSWER: yep
